ProcedureHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: PROC GDEVICE <CATALOG=<libref.>SAS-catalog> <BROWSE> <NOFS>; 
       ADD new-device-entry required-parameters <optional-parameters>;  
       COPY device-entry <FROM=<libref.>SAS-catalog> <NEWNAME=new-device-entry>;  
       DELETE device-entry;  
       FS;  
       LIST device-entry | _ALL_ | _NEXT_ | _PREV_ | DUMP>;  
       MODIFY device-entry parameter(s);
       QUIT | END | STOP;  
       RENAME device-entry NEWNAME=entry-name;  

The GDEVICE procedure is a tool for examining and changing the parameters of the graphics 
device driver catalog entries used with SAS/GRAPH software. With the GDEVICE procedure, you 
can use either the GDEVICE windows or GDEVICE procedure statements to:

  o list the device entries stored in any DEVICES catalog 
  o view the parameters for any device entry 
  o create and modify new device entries 
  o copy, modify, rename, or delete existing device entries.

StatementOptionHelp.#cdata:
Specifies whether to reverse BLACK and WHITE in the graphics output. 

SWAP does not affect the background color and only affects BLACK and WHITE foreground colors 
specified as predefined SAS color names. SWAP ignores BLACK and WHITE specified in HLS, RGB, 
or gray-scale format. This option is useful when you want to preview a graph on a video device 
and send the final copy to a printer that uses a white background. 

goptions reset=all cback=blue ctitle=black swap;
title1 h=8 'swap test';
title2 h=8 'another title';
proc gslide border;
run;

StatementHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: COPY device-entry where;

Copies a device entry and places the copy in the current catalog. The original device entry
can be either in the current catalog or in a different catalog.

